<subSubSection pageId="152" pageNumber="723" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="152.[1992,2582,2674,3100]" pageId="152" pageNumber="723">
Initially described as a subspecies of 
<taxonomicName class="Mammalia" family="Bovidae" genus="Cephalophus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Artiodactyla" pageId="152" pageNumber="723" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="ogilby">C. ogilby</taxonomicName>
:, but it now appears that the similarities between the two species are the result of convergence. Monotypic.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
